parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
the theft system light on the dashboard pops on and off
and the vehicle requires a reset by turning the key to the on position for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed, leading to potential safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: The speedometer needle reads inaccurately
sticks
or fails to work altogether
and may require multiple restarts of the engine to reset.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning headlights can cause reduced visibility, leading to potential safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: The headlights dim or fail to work altogether
and may be affected by external factors such as trees or garage roofs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause reduced visibility, leading to potential safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: The brake lights fail to turn on when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to potential accidents and safety risks.
symptoms: The ABS system locks up
causing the vehicle to slide or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter relay switch can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The engine fails to operate
and the vehicle may require a replacement of the starter relay switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel cluster can cause inaccurate readings and malfunctioning of various vehicle systems, leading to potential safety risks.
symptoms: The instrument panel lights illuminate incorrectly
and various gauges and systems may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash
despite the severity of the impact
and the vehicle's airbag warning light may be on or flashing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of airbags can cause them to deploy unexpectedly, even when the vehicle is not in a crash, or fail to deploy in the event of a crash, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags deploy unexpectedly
airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
airbag warning light is on or flashing
and the vehicle may experience electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays an improper reading
the fuel gauge needle sticks or flutters
the fuel gauge is inaccurate
the vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump failure can cause the vehicle to stall while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the fuel pump is faulty
the fuel pump module is defective
hesitation and stalling problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues can cause the vehicle to stall while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Gasoline splashes outside of the tank without warning
the fuel tank is defective
the fuel system is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission downshifting issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways or uphill.
symptoms: The transmission downshifts to 2nd gear instead of 3rd gear
the transmission surges when climbing hills
the transmission shifts up and down erratically
the engine RPM redlines to 5000 RPM
the vehicle loses power
and the cruise control disengages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways or uphill.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the transmission fails to engage
the transmission makes a loud noise
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
and the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transfer case control module failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways or uphill.
symptoms: The transmission has trouble shifting
the vehicle has trouble shifting into 4-low or 4-high gear
and the vehicle spins out of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear differential failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways or uphill.
symptoms: The vehicle has trouble shifting
the vehicle makes a loud noise
and the vehicle vibrates or shakes.
